<p>Syria and Saudi Arabia announced a new package of economic agreements on Saturday, aimed at supporting Syria’s post-war reconstruction and improving regional and international connectivity, according to multiple reports. The headline items include plans for a joint low-cost Syrian–Saudi airline and a roughly $1 billion project to upgrade Syria’s telecommunications and digital connectivity. Officials also outlined aviation work in Aleppo, including plans for a new international airport and redevelopment of the city’s existing facility. The package also includes other areas of cooperation, such as water desalination and broader development coordination.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/35Zefir0CprMdueGlnm6GN0hAx7yr1ckcogYbdB8nM_UKR_GN8jqmpcLXJTTvhR_FDbuqA1rLf8U0cSkOwvqzdO6FUBQCbhr2Xu0rzjgtvSPvvoouRYCZStLWwYGZO_SueN20ASNGbqn-M_ctFzhxDbPLBmLuXrJg2yFhGcGaP9RDuLdXdLR-o8iVgpbu8gmdLPalQ' alt='Construction workers repair a section of castle walls inside the citadel of Aleppo, Syria; the deals include work tied to Aleppo’s airport.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Sanctions shift: Multiple reports tied the deal-making push to the United States fully removing its remaining sanctions on Damascus late last year, reopening channels for international investment and transactions.</li><li>Investment fund: Saudi Investment Minister Khalid Al-Falih announced an investment fund for “major projects in Syria,” with participation from the Saudi private sector.</li><li>Airport financing: Al Jazeera reported that the Elaf fund includes $2 billion in commitments from Saudi investors for two airports in Aleppo.</li><li>Broader scope: Beyond aviation and telecoms, the two sides also signed agreements on water desalination and development cooperation.</li><li>Post-Assad context: Reports note that Syria’s new authorities took power after toppling longtime ruler Bashar al-Assad in December 2024 and have since tried to draw in foreign investment, with Saudi Arabia described as a key backer.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Syrian Investment Authority: Chief Talal al-Hilali said the agreements focus on “vital sectors” that affect daily life. He also announced a low-cost Syrian–Saudi airline to strengthen regional and international air links, alongside plans for a new international airport in Aleppo and redevelopment of the existing facility. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971696/syria-saudi-arabia-sign-joint-airline-and-telecoms-deals'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Saudi Investment Ministry: Minister Khalid Al-Falih said the agreements are meant to “build a strategic partnership,” and he announced an investment fund to support major projects in Syria with Saudi private-sector participation. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971696/syria-saudi-arabia-sign-joint-airline-and-telecoms-deals'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Syrian Telecommunications Ministry: Telecommunications Minister Abdulsalam Haykal said the SilkLink effort would be carried out with an investment of around $1 billion. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971696/syria-saudi-arabia-sign-joint-airline-and-telecoms-deals'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>New York Times analysis: The paper described the aviation and telecom deals as a sign of deepening Saudi-Syrian ties and a lift for Syria’s battered economy. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/07/world/middleeast/saudi-arabia-investment-syria-al-sharaa.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/syria-saudi-arabia-sign-joint-airline-and-telecom-project-as-damascus-pushes-post-war-reconstruction-13977337.html'>Syria, Saudi Arabia sign joint airline and telecom project as Damascus pushes post-war reconstruction</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/07/world/middleeast/saudi-arabia-investment-syria-al-sharaa.html'>Saudis Announce New Investments in Syria, a Sign of Deepening Ties</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/middle-east/article/3342788/saudi-arabia-syria-sign-telecom-and-airline-deals-sanctions-lift'>Saudi Arabia, Syria sign telecom and airline deals as sanctions lift</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/syria-and-saudi-arabia-sign-major-investment-package/a-75857509'>Syria and Saudi Arabia sign major investment package</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/middle-east/syria-saudis-sign-joint-airline-and-telecoms-deals'>Syria, Saudis sign joint airline and telecoms deals</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1971696/syria-saudi-arabia-sign-joint-airline-and-telecoms-deals'>Syria, Saudi Arabia sign joint airline and telecoms deals</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/2/7/syria-and-saudi-arabia-ink-multi-billion-dollar-investment-deals'>Syria and Saudi Arabia sign multibillion-dollar investment deals</a> - aljazeera.com</li></ul>